<task id="109" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-H-09 + D-H-10 Handler Dispatch Tests (Playbook + Chat Contexts)</title>
    <phase>Parallel — 8 Typed Tool Handlers</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>6 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>105, 106, 107, 108</dependencies>
    <blocks>none</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, integration-test</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Integration tests for existing handler code; no new production handler code; tests strengthen coverage and verify dispatch wiring. STANDARD per Spaarke task rigor table (testing tags → STANDARD).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>H-G3</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Final gate of handler workstream; sequential to ensure Wave 2 fully complete before dispatch tests run.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build the combined dispatch tests that prove each of the 8 typed handlers is reachable
    from both playbook context (via `PlaybookExecutionEngine` per FR-13–20 acceptance)
    AND chat context where applicable (handlers with `AvailableInContexts = "Both"`
    invoked via `ToolHandlerToAIFunctionAdapter`).

    This task delivers D-H-09 (playbook-context dispatch test) + D-H-10 (chat-context
    dispatch test) as a single integration-test suite in
    `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Handlers/` (or equivalent).

    Playbook dispatch test (D-H-09): for each of the 8 handlers (`DateExtractorHandler`,
    `FinancialCalculatorHandler`, `ClauseComparisonHandler`, `FinancialCalculationToolHandler`,
    `EntityExtractorHandler`, `ClauseAnalyzerHandler`, `RiskDetectorHandler`,
    `InvoiceExtractionToolHandler`), invoke via `PlaybookExecutionEngine` with a
    synthetic playbook that references the handler's `sprk_analysistool` row by
    `sprk_handlerclass`. Verify: structured output emitted; `ToolExecutionContext` correctly
    populated; LLM-assisted handlers use mocked `IOpenAiClient` for hermetic tests;
    telemetry per ADR-015.

    Chat dispatch test (D-H-10): for handlers with `AvailableInContexts = "Both"`
    (typically the 4 LLM-assisted handlers from Wave 2 — EntityExtractor, ClauseAnalyzer,
    RiskDetector, InvoiceExtraction), invoke via `ToolHandlerToAIFunctionAdapter` from
    a synthetic `ChatInvocationContext`. Verify: adapter wraps the handler as
    `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.AIFunction`; LLM sees standard function-calling tool; output
    correctly returned; safety pipeline (NFR-13) still runs.

    Each handler dispatch (playbook + chat where applicable) is a separate `[Fact]` so
    a single failure isolates to its handler. Tests run in CI per existing integration
    test pattern.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF integration-test engineer with .NET 8 + xUnit + `PlaybookExecutionEngine`
    + `ToolHandlerToAIFunctionAdapter` experience. Familiar with hermetic LLM mocking
    + synthetic playbook fixtures.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Integration tests deliver: 8 playbook-dispatch tests (one per handler) all green;
    4+ chat-dispatch tests (one per `AvailableInContexts = "Both"` handler) all green;
    each test verifies structured output + correct context population + telemetry
    compliance; LLM-assisted handlers use mocked `IOpenAiClient` (hermetic); tests run
    in CI; `code-review` recommended (STANDARD rigor — adr-check skipped per rigor table).
  </goal>

