  <context>
    <background>
      Tasks 101–108 each ship their own unit tests + contract test proving the handler
      is registered + metadata is valid + positive/error cases work. This task is the
      cross-handler integration layer — proves that the same handler, accessed via the
      playbook execution path (FR-13–20 acceptance), produces correct structured output,
      AND that handlers declared `AvailableInContexts = "Both"` are correctly wrapped
      by `ToolHandlerToAIFunctionAdapter` (FR-10) for chat dispatch.

      Combining D-H-09 + D-H-10 in one task keeps related test fixtures co-located.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
