  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL">
      Check context. If &gt;70%, run `context-handoff` then `/compact`. Declare:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD
      📋 REASON: Integration tests; testing tag → STANDARD per rigor table; no new production code
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: steps 0–10 (Step 9.5 quality gates SKIPPED per STANDARD rigor)
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read TASK-INDEX; confirm 109 is 🔲; dependencies (105, 106, 107, 108) all complete
      (Wave 2 done).
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every &lt;inputs&gt; + &lt;knowledge&gt; file. Inspect each handler's
      `sprk_analysistool` row payload (from tasks 101–108) to confirm `AvailableInContexts`
      values + `sprk_handlerclass` strings.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Author Shared Test Fixtures">
      Create `SyntheticPlaybookFixtureBuilder.cs` — builds a synthetic playbook + node
      referencing a handler by `sprk_handlerclass`; populates a `ToolExecutionContext`
      with realistic synthetic input.
      Create `MockedOpenAiClientFixture.cs` — shared hermetic LLM mock with canned
      structured outputs per handler; reusable across all LLM-assisted handler tests.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Author Playbook-Context Dispatch Tests (D-H-09)">
      Create `PlaybookContextDispatchTests.cs`. Add one `[Fact]` per handler (8 total).
      Each test: build synthetic playbook referencing handler's `sprk_handlerclass`;
      invoke via `PlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteAsync(...)`; assert structured output
      shape matches handler's output schema; assert telemetry logs handler name +
      outcome + timestamp ONLY (no input content).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Author Chat-Context Dispatch Tests (D-H-10)">
      Create `ChatContextDispatchTests.cs`. Add one `[Fact]` per handler with
      `AvailableInContexts = "Both"` (typically the 4 Wave 2 LLM-assisted handlers — but
      include all Wave 1 handlers that also declared "Both"). Each test: build synthetic
      `ChatInvocationContext`; wrap handler via `ToolHandlerToAIFunctionAdapter`; invoke
      as if LLM tool call; assert returned `AIFunction` result matches handler output;
      verify safety pipeline middleware ran (NFR-13).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify Build + Run Tests">
      `dotnet build` + `dotnet test tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/ --filter "Dispatch"`.
      All 8 playbook-dispatch tests pass; all chat-dispatch tests for "Both" handlers
      pass.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Confirm BFF Publish-Size Delta = 0">
      Confirm in task notes: BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB. Test code does not ship in
      production binary.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify CI Integration">
      Verify the new test file matches the existing integration-test naming pattern
      so it auto-runs in CI (`.github/workflows/sdap-ci.yml`).
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through criteria; record evidence in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (STANDARD rigor — SKIPPED)">
      Per STANDARD rigor table, code-review + adr-check are SKIPPED. Mark as skipped in
      notes. (Reviewer may optionally run `code-review` if test code is non-trivial.)
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status to `complete`. Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 109 🔲 → ✅. Reset
      `current-task.md`. Note in task-109-dispatch-test-evidence.md that the 8-typed-handler
      workstream is now COMPLETE.
    </step>
  </steps>

